rComments: Unpopular opinion maybe, but I truly enjoyed Prof. Bernier's class! He's a great prof and gives good feedback. I know a lot of people aren't happy with their grades on paper, but please remember it's normal to not have A's all the time... it's university!! I guess I did well in his class because I was so motivated and I truly enjoyed the class.

PLEASE save yourself and get the online version of his book! Aucun cours, juste des quiz à faire après chaque module (CTRL F pour trouver les réponses dans le livre), et 3 études de cas. Si vous avez la version papier du livre, bonne chance. Son livre est obligatoire pour la réussite du cours. Sévère dans ces corrections.

Le pire professeur que j'ai eu en 4 années d'études. professeur inexistant qui nous fait acheter son livre (seul objet pour tout, le cours, les devoirs) en fait ce cours est juste un prétexte pour cet individu de vendre son livre. Il n'y a pas de cours, il faut juste lire les chapitres. Je pourrais donner un meilleur cours que lui c'est certain!!!

This prof as an enormous Ego. In my class CMN 3505 he wanted us to buy his own book. Which is 50 dollars. The worst in all that is, all is class is online and there is no zoom meeting and he says that all we have to know is in his book. And when there is homeworks to do, they are all about his book. and of course all the examples are from his book.

He is a very respected teacher. His classes are harder than most, but he is a very good lecturer. He's a hard grader, but he will always point out what you could do to better your grade. He is also very knowledgeable in the communications and journalism world. I would recommend him to any CMN or JOU students.

Ce professeur est à éviter si vous souhaitez passer un bon semestre et maintenir votre GPA. Il est arrogant et essaie d'humilier ses étudiants; surtout si vous appartenez à la diversité canadienne. Si vous mentionnez quelque chose qui lui déplait, attendez-vous à une vengence basée sur ses propres frustrations. Ses commentaires sont insultants.

Très peu efficace pour répondre aux questions, ses réponse n'aident absolument pas à la compréhension. Il ne donne pas de cours, il donne seulement des lectures et nous devons apprendre nous-même, de plus sa correction est sévère. Je ne recommande pas du tout aucune de ses classes, surtout le cours en ligne du au manque d'information du prof .

- Expects you do tons of complicated readings a week and understand everything - Barely explains anything about the content - Get ready to teach yourself - Responds to emails and questions in the vaguest way possible (not even giving an answer sometimes) - Really hard grader - Mandatory attendance and is not very understanding about circumstances
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Horrible prof. Does not explain what he expects of his students and SUCH a hard marker. Was left feeling confused and frustrated because of his lack of instructions and clarity.

Jusqu'à maintenant, le prof répond rapidement au courriel. PAR CONTRE... c'est très ironique parce qu'il est très sévère lorsque vient le temps de la correction de grammaire.... mais ses notes/power points sont bourrés de fautes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: I took this course online, and there were no pertinent tools used, it was simply assigned textbook chapters (we read the entire thing), and then him posting additional readings. He didnt explain anything, he just gave you material and expected you to learn from it. He is also a very tough grader, and was barely ever available to meet in person :(
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: AVOID AVOID AVOID!! HE WANTS HIS STUDENTS TO FAIL!! He's extremely strict for absolutely no reason. I was warned not to take his class by plenty of people and only now do I regret not listening to them. Save yourself the misery and don't take a class with this prof. This class will drop your average for sure.

J'ai eu ce professeur dans deux cours . Il connait ce dont il traite et est intéressant en classe, mais c'est vraiment dans sa correction qu'est le problème. Je n'ai pas eu l'impression qu'on voulait me pousser à apprendre, mais plus rédiger un travail digne d'un intellectuel de son niveau. Niveau d'attente beaucoup trop exigeant.
correcte even your title page... too tough course, never want to do it again. But the good thing is, this prof reply the email in one second (online course).

I usually have high grades, but i had a tough time in these courses. Honestly this man is the worst professor that i ever had! His lecture are very long. Grammar seems to be way more important for him than the actual content; he doesn't really help you when you ask him questions, he's like "i can't give you more details"

Honestly one of the worst professors I've had in my life. Don't get me wrong, he knows what he's talking about, but has absolutely no respect for his students. He is arrogant and acts like he's king of the world. Really hope someone puts him in his place on day because it's really frustrating. Also, grammar is way more important than content right?

Now, I rarely post ratings on this site but felt this one was necessary. The course itself was very interesting although the prof seemed to enjoy correcting grammar errors more than the paper itself. I would do very good on one case study and very poorly on the next one mostly because of grammar errors. Not consistent at all and not helpful either.

Honestly, I really liked him! He helped me out when I had questions, the material is interesting and the case studies really helped me learn about the material. It's not an easy class, but if you give it your all you can do good.
Plus pire professeur de mon séjour a l'université d'Ottawa. A ÉVITER SI POSSIBLE !!!  Il passe plus de temps a corriger les fautes d'orthographes que le travail.

Horrible prof. Very inconsiderate & stuckup. He's useless as a teacher. Doesn't help his students. You'd think he'd be more helpful for it being an online course. Not available for his office hours, nor does he bother telling you if he'll be away during his office hours. I recommend to not take this class! Material is very interesting, not him.
Probably one of the most inconsiderate teachers ever. Mistakes all over his powerpoints; it's aweful.

Prof est insultant. Ne se soucie pas de ses élèves. Passe plus de temps a corriger les erreurs d'orthographes que le travail même. Cependant, il était un journaliste donc il connais sa matière et utilise plusieurs cas intéressants
Worst teacher ever. Please avoid for your own good :)

Excellent prof - Un des meilleur qu ej'ai eu. Très organisé, très impliqué.  Ancien journaliste, donc il comprend les 2 cotés de la médaille, il agit souvent d'ailleurs comme spécialiste du journalisme et de l'éthique en cours de justice.
One of the worst teacher that I had to date. Please avoid him!

Abolute boredom :S  He doesn't seem to care a whole lot about the students... What COULD be a sense of humor actually seems like arrogance..and I felt he LOVED to make fun of students.  To be avoided.
Il est sincèrement le pire prof que jai eu à date. En plus denseigner mal, il na aucune personnalité.
Un prof exigeant pour lui comme pour ses étudiants. Ses idées sont claires et il a de l'expérience professionnelle en plus.
No Comments
Yah! I agree with everybody avoid!!
Worst.teacher.ever
Why is he teaching if he hates students? Though he seems to know a lot about journalism, you know there's something wrong when he doesn't even know who Max Keeping is...

Monsieur Bernier what you need is to apply your ethical notions to your pratices. A little bit of humbleness and humanity is much needed from a man who speaks about justice and beeing ethical. I mean, who gives his own book to buy & read for his ethical class, isn't that biased and unethical???? I don't understand profs who want to fail students?
The guy has the experience, but can accept that others do differently than him.  Corrections from hell!  Bases his teachings on opinions instead of actual facts.

He was such a hard grader... Seriously, if you have the option to take ANY of the classes he teaches in englsih... i would STRONGLY suggest you do so.  Nobody i know got more then a C+ in any of his classes.  I think that speaks for itself!

This guy has a huge ego and loves to boast about his past accomplishements, he doesn't aim to provide incite by relating the course to his personnal experiences instead he vowes to sooth his need for attention. Hard grader who thinks he's the greatest prof on earth. Avoid unless desperate.

I STRONGLY suggest taking this class in english if you have take it, he is really hard on french writting skills.. basically expects you to write like him and will tell you that you suck if you don't. Funny at times.. but I wouldn't risk it ever again!
This prof shares good anecdotes and succeeds in making ethics fun and interesting. He expects as much from students as he puts into the class.
